# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DAREBIN BUSINESS DIRECTORY - SERVER-SIDE ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file lists all the secret keys and variables your application needs to run.
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. DO NOT commit this file with your actual keys to a public repository.
# 2. RENAME this file to ".env" in your local development environment.
# 3. FILL IN the placeholder values below with your actual credentials.
#

# --- STRIPE API ---
# Get these from your Stripe Dashboard: https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys
# The Secret Key is used for all server-side Stripe API calls.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...

# The Webhook Secret is used to verify that incoming webhook events are genuinely from Stripe.
# Get this from your webhook endpoint settings in the Stripe Dashboard.
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...

# --- AUSTRALIAN BUSINESS REGISTER (ABR) ---
# Used for the ABN validation feature.
# You can request a GUID for the free ABR Data Services here:
# https://www.abr.gov.au/abr-data-services/how-use-services/requesting-guid
ABR_GUID=YOUR_GUID_HERE

# --- FIREBASE ADMIN SDK ---
# This is required for server-side actions, like the admin dashboard functions.
# 1. Go to your Firebase project settings -> Service accounts.
# 2. Click "Generate new private key". A JSON file will be downloaded.
# 3. Copy the ENTIRE content of that JSON file and paste it here as a single-line string.
#    It must be enclosed in single quotes. Example: '{"type": "service_account", ...}'
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY='{}'

# --- ADMIN BOOTSTRAP (PRODUCTION ONLY) ---
# Enables a secure, one-time admin grant via /api/admin/grant in production.
# Set a strong random token and the specific email allowed to be promoted.
# If these are not set, the endpoint is blocked in production.
ADMIN_BOOTSTRAP_TOKEN=
ADMIN_BOOTSTRAP_EMAIL=

# --- FIREBASE STORAGE ---
# The name of your Firebase Storage bucket.
# You can find this in your Firebase Console -> Storage -> Files tab.
# It usually looks like `your-project-id.appspot.com`.
FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
